{"parse":{"title":"Razai","pageid":27758612,"revid":827514132,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">For the second president of Iran, see <a href=\"/wiki/Mohammad-Ali_Rajai\" title=\"Mohammad-Ali Rajai\">Mohammad-Ali Rajai</a>.</div>\n<p><b>Razai</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Hindustani_language\" title=\"Hindustani language\">Hindustani</a>: \u0930\u091c\u093c\u093e\u0908; \u0631\u0632\u0627\u0626\u06cc, <a href=\"/wiki/Sylheti_language\" title=\"Sylheti language\">Sylheti</a>: <span lang=\"syl\">\ua81e\ua823\ua80e\ua823\ua801</span>,  <i>ruh-zaa-ee</i>; or \u0a30\u0a1c\u0a3e\u0a08, <i>Ra-jaa-ee</i> in <a href=\"/wiki/Punjabi_language\" title=\"Punjabi language\">Punjabi</a>) is a <a href=\"/wiki/Quilt\" title=\"Quilt\">bedquilt</a> used in <a href=\"/wiki/Afghanistan\" title=\"Afghanistan\">Afghanistan</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Iran\" title=\"Iran\">Iran</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Pakistan\" title=\"Pakistan\">Pakistan</a>,  <a href=\"/wiki/North_India\" title=\"North India\">North India</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Sylhet_region\" title=\"Sylhet region\">Sylhet</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Nepal\" title=\"Nepal\">Nepal</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-pennell1912_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-pennell1912-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> It is a type of <a href=\"/wiki/Bedding\" title=\"Bedding\">bedding</a> similar to a <a href=\"/wiki/Duvet\" title=\"Duvet\">duvet</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/Comforter\" title=\"Comforter\">comforter</a>. <i>Razais</i> usually have a <a href=\"/wiki/Cotton\" title=\"Cotton\">cotton</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Silk\" title=\"Silk\">silk</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/Velvet\" title=\"Velvet\">velvet</a> cover which is stuffed with <a href=\"/wiki/Cotton_wool\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Cotton wool\">cotton wool</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-pennell1912_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-pennell1912-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> They can provide a great deal of warmth even in the very cold weather that can occur in these regions, primarily due to the <a href=\"/wiki/Thermal_insulation\" title=\"Thermal insulation\">insulating effects</a> of the large amount of air trapped in the cotton wool.<sup id=\"cite_ref-murray1924_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-murray1924-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Maintenance\">Maintenance</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Razai&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Maintenance\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The cotton wool in a <i>razai</i> clumps over time, thinning the <i>razai</i> and driving the air out, which causes the <i>razai</i> to become less effective as a protection against the cold. For this reason, prior to the onset of winter weather, it is common for families to get their <i>razais</i> <a href=\"/wiki/Carding\" title=\"Carding\">carded</a>: the cotton wool in the <i>razai</i> is removed, carded to eliminate the clumping, and reinserted into the <i>razai</i>-cover.<sup id=\"cite_ref-hankin1994_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-hankin1994-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> This is done by <i>razai</i>-carders (called <i>dhuniyas</i> or <i>dhunnas</i>, see the <a href=\"/wiki/Australian_English\" title=\"Australian English\">Australian English</a> term for duvet, \"<a href=\"/wiki/Doona\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Doona\">doona</a>\") who are professionally adept and seasonally employed in this activity.<sup id=\"cite_ref-balfour1899_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-balfour1899-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-eafcs1959_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-eafcs1959-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> The bowed carding instrument, called the <i>dhunki</i>, has a distinctive twang when it is in use or its string is plucked.<sup id=\"cite_ref-balfour1899_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-balfour1899-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> This twang is a common daytime sound in rural areas in the autumn, and is sometimes used as a cultural reference to the onset of winter in local literature and movies.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Business\">Business</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Razai&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Business\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Many businesses have been set up to sell quilts. The quilt market is big, and culture and local customs have evolved to make quilts into an international business opportunity.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Razai&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-pennell1912-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-pennell1912_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-pennell1912_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFTheodore_Leighton_Pennell1912\" class=\"citation\">Theodore Leighton Pennell (1912), <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=1KVJAAAAIAAJ\"><i>Things seen in northern India</i></a>, Dutton, <q><i>... The other article which travellers are recommended to purchase in India is a native quilt, or \"razai.\" This is a cotton or silk cover stuffed with cotton-wool ...</i></q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Things+seen+in+northern+India&amp;rft.pub=Dutton&amp;rft.date=1912&amp;rft.au=Theodore+Leighton+Pennell&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D1KVJAAAAIAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARazai\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-murray1924-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-murray1924_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=BU2tV-yRr4gC\"><i>Murray's handbook, India, Burma &amp; Ceylon</i></a>, John Murray, 1924, <q><i>... which in North India may sometimes be bitterly cold. The minimum equipment is a pillow and two cotton-wadded quilts (razais), one to sleep on, and one, which should be larger, as a coverlet ...</i></q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Murray%27s+handbook%2C+India%2C+Burma+%26+Ceylon&amp;rft.pub=John+Murray&amp;rft.date=1924&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DBU2tV-yRr4gC&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARazai\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-hankin1994-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-hankin1994_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFNigel_B._Hankin1994\" class=\"citation\">Nigel B. Hankin (1994), <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=rEZeAAAAIAAJ\"><i>Hanklyn-Janklin, or, A stranger's rumble-tumble guide to some words, customs and quiddities Indian and Indo-British</i></a>, Banyan Books, <q><i>... Each autumn the razai is unquilted and the cotton carded and fluffed ...</i></q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Hanklyn-Janklin%2C+or%2C+A+stranger%27s+rumble-tumble+guide+to+some+words%2C+customs+and+quiddities+Indian+and+Indo-British&amp;rft.pub=Banyan+Books&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.au=Nigel+B.+Hankin&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DrEZeAAAAIAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARazai\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-balfour1899-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-balfour1899_4-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-balfour1899_4-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFHenry_Balfour1899\" class=\"citation\">Henry Balfour (1899), <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=zM8TAAAAYAAJ\"><i>The natural history of the musical bow</i></a>, Clarendon, <q><i>... the itinerant cotton-cleaner, dhuniya. as he goes his rounds along the streets, constantly twangs the tightly stretched string of his huge cotton-cleaning bow, dhunki, which gives out a musical note serving in lieu of a street call ...</i></q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+natural+history+of+the+musical+bow&amp;rft.pub=Clarendon&amp;rft.date=1899&amp;rft.au=Henry+Balfour&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DzM8TAAAAYAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARazai\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-eafcs1959-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-eafcs1959_5-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=i3ALAAAAIAAJ\"><i>The Eastern anthropologist, Volume 13</i></a>, Ethnographic and Folk-Culture Society (Lucknow, India), 1959, <q><i>... The profession of cotton carding is mainly seasonal&#160;; a Dhuniya is usually employed in his specific occupation just ... During the major part of the year a Dhuniya earns his living by other means ...</i></q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Eastern+anthropologist%2C+Volume+13&amp;rft.pub=Ethnographic+and+Folk-Culture+Society+%28Lucknow%2C+India%29&amp;rft.date=1959&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3Di3ALAAAAIAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARazai\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Flag_of_India.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/41/Flag_of_India.svg/25px-Flag_of_India.svg.png\" width=\"25\" height=\"17\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/41/Flag_of_India.svg/38px-Flag_of_India.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/41/Flag_of_India.svg/50px-Flag_of_India.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1350\" data-file-height=\"900\" /></a></td><td><i>This article about the culture of India is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Razai&amp;action=edit\">expanding it</a>.</i><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\" style=\"position: absolute; right: 15px; display: none;\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:India-culture-stub\" title=\"Template:India-culture-stub\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:India-culture-stub\" title=\"Template talk:India-culture-stub\"><abbr title=\"Discuss this template\">t</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-edit\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/in